# Unix packer

Package manager for unix soul

## FEATURES
- if a package is installed then don't install it
- needs git to clone the configuration of package
- if a user doesn't want to clone full repository as it might be too large (all just download of the repo)
- makes heavy use of git
- load previous versions
- update a package
- allow user to choose the dir to save all repos of package
- mostly work like lazy.nvim
- If something needs build dependencies then they can create a configuration file just like requirements.txt
- Manage profiles from different directories
- keep track of installed plugins
- can install configurations && tools for which configuration is available

> only installs the configurations that are specific to the unix soul
